        "AyahNumber": 1,
        "Tafseer": "1. Analysis of Words and Explanation of Verses\n\nThe revelation of the Book is from Allah, the Exalted in Might, the Wise. (1)\n\nConsolation for the Prophet (pbuh) and a Warning for the Deniers\n\nWe have explained the analysis of the word 'Tanzeel' (revelation) in its proper place—stating that its meaning is not merely sending down, but sending down with elaborate care. This introductory verse contains, within itself, consolation for the Prophet (pbuh) and a threat and warning for the deniers of the Qur'an. The aspect of consolation for the Prophet (pbuh) is: 'You have neither composed this Book yourself, nor have you asked God to send it down upon you of your own accord; rather, your Lord Himself has sent it down and is sending it down upon you with highly elaborate care, step by step, so rest assured that He Himself will manifest its truths and He Himself will pave the way for it.' The God Who has sent down this Book is no helpless being, but 'Al-Aziz'—meaning the Dominant and Powerful. He can do whatever He wills, and no one can obstruct His will. But along with being Exalted in Might, He is also Wise ('Al-Hakeem'); for this reason, if some obstructions are faced in the path now or will be faced in the future, attribute them to the wisdom of God. Nothing happens without the command of God, and His every action is based on wisdom and purpose.\n\nThe aspect of warning for its deniers is: Allah Almighty is sending down this Book with highly elaborate care and graduation for the guidance of people. Its right is that people value this blessing and obtain guidance and light from it. If, contrary to this, they adopt the path of denial, they must remember that this is not the request of a petitioner, but the command of the Exalted in Might, the Wise God, which must be obeyed. He can do whatever He wills. If, despite this, He is granting respite to the deniers, He is doing so merely under the requirements of His wisdom."
