    {
        "SurahNumber": 39,
        "AyahNumber": 2,
        "Tafseer": "\"Indeed, We have revealed to you the Book in truth, so worship Allah, [being] sincere to Him in religion.\" (2)\n\n'Truth' (Al-Haqq) here means the decisive word, and 'religion' (Ad-Deen) means obedience. The explanation of the various meanings of these words has occurred in their proper places.\n\nThe Decisive Word in the Matter of Tawhid and Shirk\n\nAddressing the Prophet (pbuh), He stated: We have sent down this Book to you with the decisive word. The differences which innovators and polytheists had created regarding the Tawhid of Allah, this Book has decided them; so worship Allah, being sincere to Him in obedience. Allah alone is the deserving recipient of sincere obedience; He is the Creator and Sustainer of everyone, so He alone is the deserving recipient of everyone's worship, and He Who is the deserving recipient of worship is also the deserving recipient of obedience. It is entirely absurd that the deserving recipient of worship is one, while the deserving recipient of obedience becomes someone else; and just as worship must be sincere, obedience must also be unmixed. The obedience of anyone else besides Allah, contrary to the obedience of Allah, is not permissible.\n\nAddressing the Prophet (pbuh) to state this means that after the sending down of this Book, your path has been specified. Walk upon this path; if others join you, well and good, and if they do not, leave them to their state. You carry no responsibility for them."
