    {
        "SurahNumber": 39,
        "AyahNumber": 3,
        "Tafseer": "\"Unquestionably, for Allah is the pure religion. And those who take protectors besides Him [say], 'We only worship them that they may bring us nearer to Allah in position.' Indeed, Allah will judge between them concerning that over which they differ. Indeed, Allah does not guide one who is a liar and [confirmed] disbeliever.\" (3)\n\nThat is, those who have taken protectors besides Allah, and have invented this philosophy in their favor—claiming that they are worshipping them not as gods but as a means of proximity to God, if they are not accepting the decision of this Book, Allah will judge their differences on the Day of Judgment.\n\n'Indeed, Allah does not guide one who is a liar and [confirmed] disbeliever.' 'Yahdee' (guide) is used in various places in the Qur'an in the sense of making someone successful in an objective. Its explanation has passed in its proper place.\n\nRegarding the decision of these people on the Day of Judgment, He clarified this basic reality: those who are liars and ungrateful, Allah Almighty will not make them successful. 'Liar' refers to those who fabricated this lie against God—claiming that He has made such and such His partners, whereas God has sent down no proof or testimony in their favor. 'Ungrateful' refers to those who received all blessings from God, but sang the praises of others. Both of these attributes belong to the polytheists, and both are necessarily found in every polytheist simultaneously. It states that these people are denying the Qur'an and the Prophet on this arrogance: that when the Resurrection occurs, they will achieve proximity to God through their deities, whereas no hope of such liars and ungrateful ones will ever be realized with God."
