    {
        "SurahNumber": 39,
        "AyahNumber": 4,
        "Tafseer": "\"If Allah had intended to take a son, He could have chosen from what He creates whatever He willed. Exalted is He; He is Allah, the One, the Prevailing.\" (4)\n\nA Satire on the Belief of the Polytheists\n\nThis is a satire on the belief of the Arab polytheists—who believed the angels to be the daughters of God, worshipped them, and considered them a means of proximity to God. These simpletons did not even think: if God had intended to take progeny, why would He choose daughters; He would choose from His creation whatever best thing He willed for Himself! 'Exalted is He' (Subhanahu)—He is pure from such relationships and such needs. He stands in no need of any son, daughter, partner, or helper. He is entirely One, and He keeps His entire creation under His control."
