    {
        "SurahNumber": 39,
        "AyahNumber": 5,
        "Tafseer": "\"He created the heavens and the earth in truth. He wraps the night over the day and wraps the day over the night and has subjected the sun and the moon, each running [its course] for a specified term. Unquestionably, He is the Exalted in Might, the Forgiving.\" (5)\n\nThe Belief of Shirk and Intercession is Contrary to this World's Being with Truth\n\nHe has not created the heavens and the earth without purpose and wisdom, such that there is no distinction between goodness and evil, and truth and falsehood within them—allowing whoever wants to secure high ranks for themselves with God through intercession, regardless of their deeds and beliefs. If this were so, this world would be reduced to a completely purposeless workshop, which is entirely contrary to the majesty of a Wise and Just Creator.\n\nAllah Almighty is Not Unconcerned with this World\n\n'He wraps the night over the day...'—meaning let no one remain in the misconception that God, after creating the world, is sitting aside as a mere spectator; rather, He continuously wraps the night over the day and wraps the day over the night. He alone has subjected the sun and the moon, and all are revolving in accordance with their specified system of times. It is impossible for a difference of a minute or second to appear in their discipline of time.\n\n'Unquestionably, He is the Exalted in Might, the Forgiving'—meaning open your ears and hear well that God is both Exalted in Might (Al-Aziz) and Forgiving (Al-Ghaffar). He is Exalted in Might; therefore, no one can achieve access to Him without His permission, nor can anyone intercede for anyone. And He is Forgiving; therefore, He Himself will forgive those who establish their entitlement to His forgiveness. They will not stand in need of any intercessor's intercession."
