        "Tafseer": "\"They will have canopies of fire above them and below them, canopies. By that Allah threatens His servants. O My servants, then fear Me.\" (16)\n\n'Zulal' is the plural of 'zullah'. Its primary meaning is a canopy or covering. This describes the fate of those losers who were mentioned in the preceding verse. It states: for them will be the covering of fire and its bedding. Fire will wrap them layer upon layer from above and from below. It states: this is what Allah is warning His servants of—meaning this is no ordinary thing which can be brushed off in jest. After this, in a highly compassionate tone, He stated: 'O My servants, this is highly severe, so fear My punishment!'"
