    {
        "SurahNumber": 39,
        "AyahNumber": 17,
        "Tafseer": "\"But those who have avoided Taghut, lest they worship it, and turned back to Allah - for them are glad tidings. So give glad tidings to My servants Who listen to speech and follow the best of it. Those are the ones Allah has guided, and those are people of understanding.\" (17-18)\n\nThe analysis of the word 'Taghut' has passed under verse 256 of Surah Al-Baqarah and verse 51 of Surah An-Nisa'. This is a comprehensive word to describe everything other than Allah, whether they are idols, Jinn, devils, or leaders who turn people away from the worship and obedience of Allah.\n\nThe Attributes and Glad Tidings of Those Who Achieve Success\n\nIn contrast to the losers, this is the mention of those who achieve success; they are blessed with the glad tidings of eternal success, and their attributes due to which they became deserving of this glad tidings are praised. It states: Our servants who avoid the worship of everything other than Allah, and turn to Allah with complete sincerity, for them are glad tidings; so give glad tidings of eternal success to My servants.\n\n'Who listen to speech and follow the best of it...'—this describes their upright nature due to which they became deserving of God's guidance and His glad tidings. It states: their condition is not such that when some word is presented before them, before listening to and understanding it, they stand up to fight with the speaker, but they listen to the word with attention and follow every good word. 'Those are the ones Allah has guided'—meaning as a reward for this upright nature of theirs, Allah Almighty blessed them with the guidance of the Qur'an.\n\n'and those are people of understanding'—it states that these are indeed the wise, and only the wise can benefit from the reminder of God. This is the very same point which passed above in verse 8: 'Only they will remember who are people of understanding,' and which is expressed in Surah Sad as follows: '[This is] a blessed Book which We have revealed to you, [O Muhammad], that they might reflect upon its verses and that those of understanding would be reminded.' (29)."
